wiki.text:
'23199 Bezdek' is a main belt asteroid with an orbital period of 1936.3988715
days (5.30 years).<ref name="JP: Small-body Database Browser"></ref>

The asteroid was discovered by the Lincoln Near-Earth Asteroid Research project
in Socorro, New Mexico on September 3, 2000. It is named after Daniel Karoly
Bezdek, who won second place at the 2007 Intel International Science and
Engineering Fair. His father Károly Bezdek is a professor of mathematics at the
University of Calgary.
